<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7701347>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Tetrias: A, T. fischerii (A. Milne-Edwards, 1867), syntype, MNHN B-3921, female, 8.2 × 14.6 mm, New Caledonia; B, T. fischerii, CBM ZC 17320, ovigerous female, 7.0 × 12.1 mm, Iriomote Island, Ryukyu Islands; C, T. fischerii, CBM ZC 17320, male, 7.2 × 10.6 mm, Iriomote Island, Ryukyu Islands; D, T. scabripes Rathbun, 1898, holotype, US 21595, ovigerous female, 5.8 × 9.8 mm, Gulf of California; E, Tetrias sp., CBM-ZC 7625, 4.5 × 6.5 mm, Kerama Island, Ryukyu Islands." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7701347/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7701349>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Cephalothorax and third maxilliped (mxp3) of Tetrias fischerii (A. Milne-Edwards, 1867). A–B, T. fischerii, RUMF-ZC-5924, male, 8.0 × 11.6 mm, Iriomote Island, Ryukyu Islands (setae of left mxp3 partially trimmed); C–E, T. fischerii, RUMF-ZC-5928, male, 7.6 × 10.6 mm, Iriomote Island, Ryukyu Islands. A, cephalothorax, anterior view; B, cephalothorax, anteroventral view; C, mxp 3, left, outer view (setae not trimmed); D, mxp 3, left, outer view (setae partially trimmed); E, mxp 3, left, inner-lateral view. (c, carpus; d, dactylus; e, exopod; epm, epistome posterior margin; i, ischium; m, merus; p, propodus; pm, pterygostomial margin; s, suture between merus and ischium)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7701349/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7701351>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4.Anterior part of cephalothorax and appendages of Tetrias fischerii (A. Milne-Edwards, 1867), RUMF-ZC-5924, left side, male, 8.0 × 11.6 mm, Iriomote Island, Ryukyu Islands (setae trimmed). A, anterior view; B, anteroventral view. (a1, antennal article 1; epm, epistome posterior margin; pm, pterygostomial margin. Arrowhead, proximolateral protrusion from antennal article 1)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7701351/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7701353>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Cephalothorax and third maxilliped (mxp3) of Sakaina yokoyai (Glassell, 1933), RUMF-ZC-5827, female, 6.5 × 10.2 mm, Oshoro, Hokkaido. A, cephalothorax, anteroventral view; B, mxp 3, left, outer view (setae partially trimmed); C, mxp 3, left, inner view. c, carpus; d, dactylus; e, exopod; epm, epistome posterior margin; im, ischiomerus; p, propodus; pm, pterygostomial margin." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7701353/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

